        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The _sendMail() function doesnt check if mail() is actually available. When I run it on my local XAMPP installation I don't have the mail-function available and it will return an error about that. If the mail would have the error surpressed I will get an exception. So, please place @'s before the mail() functions so I can catch the exception without getting extra errors\/warnings. Simple fix I guess :)"
